    {"question": "What are Level I versus Level II oncoplastic techniques?", "answer": "Level I: volume displacement (glandular rearrangement, simple advancement/rotation of remaining tissue) for excisions <20% of breast volume. Level II: volume displacement with skin resection patterns (reduction mammoplasty, mastopexy) or volume replacement (local flaps, fat grafting) for excisions 20-50%. Level II typically requires contralateral symmetry procedure."},
